      "intro": "If your parent is 60+ and struggles to shop or prepare nutritious meals, Meals on Wheels delivers hot lunches directly to their home Monday through Friday. Because the program serves homebound seniors regardless of income, your parent likely qualifies if they can't safely get to the store or cook for themselves.\n\nEach meal meets one-third of daily nutritional requirements and is low in sodium, fat, and sugar. Special diets are available for diabetes and heart disease. Because drivers provide a daily safety check-in, you'll have peace of mind knowing someone sees your parent every weekday.\n\nMassachusetts serves over 30,000 meals daily through local providers. Contact your local Area Agency on Aging to apply — no statewide income limits apply, though some providers may charge a small fee based on ability to pay.",
