      "intro": "If your parent has Alzheimer's or dementia and lives at home in Massachusetts, you may qualify for free respite care services through the Family Caregiver Support Program. This program provides home health aides, personal care assistance, companion services, and specialized dementia coaching to give family caregivers regular breaks.\n\nThe program serves people age 60+ or any age with an Alzheimer's or dementia diagnosis who live at home (not in nursing homes or assisted living). Services include respite care, homemaker help, chore services, and complex care training for family members. Because this connects to the broader Family Caregiver Support Program, your parent can access multiple services through one local coordinator rather than navigating separate programs.\n\nEligibility focuses on diagnosis and functional need rather than income limits. Services are provided through local Aging Service Access Points (ASAPs) across Massachusetts, so availability and providers may vary by region.",
